    "macroSummary": "Headlines show a classic bear market relief rally driven by cooling CPI data (60-year record gas price decline) and easing geopolitical tensions from US-Iran talks, pushing Bitcoin above $73K and equities higher. However, the fundamental bear market structure remains intact with Treasury data showing record debt service costs ($623B YTD) and elevated tariff revenues (+272% YTD) signaling ongoing structural pressures.",
    "regimeImpact": "Bear market relief rally assessment remains unchanged as oil dropping on Mideast talks and cooling inflation are temporary relief factors, not structural regime changers.",
    "actionItems": [
      "Maintain BMNR cash-secured put ladder as Bitcoin volatility ($72K-$73K range) creates premium opportunities while staying above $62,300 structural level",
      "Monitor April 2 tariff deadline closely as Treasury data shows massive tariff revenue increases (+272% YTD) suggesting trade tensions remain elevated",
      "Prepare for potential reversal as $2.2B crypto options expiry and CPI-driven rally may face resistance at technical levels"
    ],
    "keySignals": [
      "Oil dropping on US-Iran talks reduces stagflation risk but geopolitical premium remains elevated",
      "CPI cooling with 60-year record gas price decline supports risk assets temporarily but doesn't change Fed policy trajectory",
      "Bitcoin breaking $73K on inflation data shows crypto benefiting from both debasement fears and risk-on flows",
      "Record Treasury debt service costs ($623B YTD +7%) highlight structural fiscal deterioration despite temporary revenue gains"
    ]
